Sentencas: A Ni0.95La0.05O-SDC composite was tested as solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) anode fueled with methane at temperatures between 500 and 600 degrees C (i.e. for low temperature SOFC).
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane

Sentencas: It was found that NiO and La2O3 formed a solid solution and small amounts of La2NiO4 were also observed after sintering at 1340 degrees C. After subsequent reduction.
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane

Sentencas: NiO was reduced to Ni while La2O3 remained as oxide phase.
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane

Sentencas: The La modified NiO-SDC anode showed higher OCV, over 30% improved maximum power density and better stability in humidified methane fuel as compared with the NiO-SDC anode.
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane

Sentencas: Meanwhile, the Ni0.95La0.05O-SDC anode cell displayed lower polarization resistance (e.g. at 600 degrees C, 0.12 Omega cm(-2) versus 0.34 Omega cm(-2) for NiO-SDC) implying higher surface reaction activity than the NiO-SDC anode cell.
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane

Sentencas: At 600 degrees C. the Ni0.95La0.05O-SDC anode exhibited similar performance and activity in H-2 and CH4 fuels.
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane

Sentencas: The SEM results indicated that La effectively prevented NiO coarsening giving rise to a much finer structure with smaller particle size and more uniform distribution, which can contribute to the better performance with La. (C) 2011
Titulo: Lanthanum promoted NiO-SDC anode for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells fueled with methane
